  },
  "doc": {
    "runtime": "Linux executes the source-built RetroArch and cores inside bubblewrap, with the AppImage Nix closure and packaged generic Mesa nixGL wrapper mounted read-only. No host RetroArch app or Flatpak runtime participates.",
    "input": "The declared action set is the exact RetroArch profile/watcher capability surface. Linux uses SDL2 port 1 (joypad index 0) with autodetection and the packaged 28de:11ff aliases; it deliberately has no name-based device reservation because Steam Game Mode exposes the same virtual pad under multiple SDL names. Only autoconfiguration notifications are suppressed.",
    "frame_output": "The Linux GL2/GL3 package calls the directly linked Semu renderer once after the game renderchain draw and once after RetroArch overlays, menu, widgets, and OSD. RetroArch native shaders and filtering stay disabled so the renderer owns shader, bezel, and Semu menu composition without suppressing either phase while RetroArch's menu is active. The macOS Metal path remains outside this OpenGL integration.",
    "state": "data_home=xdg confines RetroArch config, data, and cache writes to its Semu-owned state root; saves, states, screenshots, and firmware use their separately declared paths.",
    "sandbox_linux": "Project, assets, ROMs, BIOS, host OS, and the Nix store are read-only; parent binds precede the narrower Semu-owned writable overlays.",
    "sandbox_macos": "The packaged source build, ROMs, firmware, project, and assets are read-only. HOME and the active RetroArch config are redirected beneath the per-emulator state root, the only writable path."
  }
}
